Integrate Gemma Rescue Grid as a second dashboard tab

Adds an offline-edge flood-response track alongside the existing live
NASA FIRMS wildfire-monitoring track. Both share the NusaSiaga shell.
The dashboard now opens with a tab pill at the top: Wildfire Monitoring
(NASA FIRMS) and Flood Response Demo (Gemma 4 synthesis).

Nothing in the existing wildfire work is changed - the NASA FIRMS API
route, the dashboard-hotspots loader, the original maps, incidents,
hazard panel, environment stats, and report grid all stay exactly as
NoesaaDecodes shipped them. The wildfire view simply got moved into
a composition component (WildfireView) and the page renders it as
one of the two tab children.

The flood track is new and additive:

New library files:
  src/lib/types.ts                  TypeScript mirrors of the
                                    Pydantic schemas in the
                                    gemma-disaster-grid repo
  src/lib/synthesis-scenario-a.ts   CommandCenterSynthesis output
                                    from Gemma 4 E4B on Colab
                                    (will be regenerated from 31B
                                    on Kaggle for the final submission)
  src/lib/flood-reports.ts          12 EdgeTriageReport objects from
                                    Scenario A (renamed export to
                                    floodReports so it coexists with
                                    the existing reports.ts that holds
                                    wildfire mock data)

New components under src/features/flood/components/:
  FloodHero            Synthesis-driven metrics for the flood tab
  FloodSampleCard      One feature EdgeTriageReport rendered as the
                       sample card on the hero
  FloodMap             Jakarta-centered map shell
  FloodMapClient       Severity-colored markers for 12 reports
  FloodMapLegend       Severity 1-5 legend
  FloodSynthesisPanel  Full CommandCenterSynthesis dashboard: severity
                       distribution, vulnerable groups, priority zones,
                       recommended actions, validity flags, confidence
                       notes
  FloodReportFeed      Reverse-chronological list of EdgeTriageReports
  FloodReportCard      One report rendered with severity, evac priority,
                       hazards, and routing-lane badge
  FloodStats           Disaster-response metric cards derived from
                       the synthesis
  FloodView            Composition for the flood tab

Wildfire composition:
  src/features/wildfire/components/WildfireView.tsx
    Wraps DashboardOverview + DisasterMap + HazardAnalysisPanel +
    EnvironmentStats + IncidentFeed + DemoReadinessPanel + ReportGrid +
    LocalAiMode (all unchanged from the prior wildfire build).

Tab switcher:
  src/features/dashboard/components/TabbedDashboard.tsx
    Client component. Takes both tab children as ReactNodes (so server
    children can be passed through). Defaults to Flood Response Demo
    so a fresh open lands on the Gemma 4 story.

Updated:
  src/app/page.tsx           Now wraps WildfireView and FloodView in
                             TabbedDashboard. Keeps the same NASA
                             FIRMS server-side fetch with fallback.
  src/app/layout.tsx         Title and description reflect both tracks.
  src/components/shared/AppHeader.tsx
                             Brand line: NusaSiaga - Gemma Rescue Grid.
  src/features/offline/components/OfflineResiliencePanel.tsx
                             Now describes the hybrid Gemma 4 edge +
                             cloud architecture. Shared across tabs.
  README.md                  Full dual-track rewrite with architecture
                             diagram and credit to both founders.

Verified: npm install (passed earlier), tsc --noEmit clean,
npm run build produces 5 static pages.

Code repo for the gemma-disaster-grid side:
https://github.com/listyantidewi1/gemma-disaster-grid
